ELF
Taxes
Generally, people whose tax affairs are straightforward
do not have to complete a self-assessment form, because
there is no more tax to pay. However, thousands of taxpayers who have not received a form may be missing out on
substantial refunds because they have paid too much tax.
Those most at risk of losing out include people who have
stopped working in the middle of a tax year and whose
annual allowances have been apportioned for only part of
the year, and casual or “portfolio” workers who might have
several jobs simultaneously.
